programmes.show_description: The Poseidon Crew recruit a 14-year-old worker to help speed up their operation. Meanwhile, the Gold Timers are slowed down by a freak dust storm. S6, Ep15
The Final Fight. After a shock exit, the remaining survivalists face a brutal two-day water extraction journey. Electric eels, anaconda and caiman all pose threats in this finale. S2, Ep8
Eye Of The Storm. A wild child and retired sergeant are stranded in the Belize jungle after a catastrophic hurricane that threatens their entire challenge. How will they get on? S3, Ep2

Taylor Family Farm. The team heads to Yorktown to pick through an old farm and former Native American settlement. Mike and Tay handle the heavy lifting outside to save a steel boat. S9, Ep12
Marine Salvage. Mike and Robert head to Florida and get lessons in diving and safety so they can salvage under water. They recover old ship parts from the bottom of the ocean. S9, Ep13
Russian Roulette. Cornelia co-captains, Josh and Casey, risk a 500-mile trek north to the Russian line. Meanwhile, captain Keith struggles with a broken boat and a broken heart. S15, Ep10
Curse Of The Russian Line. The winter season strikes the fleet with brutal Storm Elsa. And, Josh and Casey haul their all-time biggest pots, starting a gold rush to the Russian Line. S15, Ep11
Hell Hath No Fury. The wrath of Arctic storm Elsa hits the Cornelia hardest as a breakaway pot thrashes Josh and Casey's crew. And, the icy blasts threaten to capsize the Wizard. S15, Ep12
Sixty Foot Monster. As arctic superstorm Elsa intensifies, a rare forecast warns of huge waves. Trapped in the crab-rich northern grounds, one boat faces a 60-foot monster. S15, Ep13
Bad Luck. The Opal Whispers are forced to leave behind a rich opal seam in a mine on the verge of collapse. The Cheals are cut off from their mine by crippling floods. S6, Ep5
Start Again From The Beginning. Gale force winds threaten the Digi Diggers' dreams of an eco-mine. The Bushmen discover dangerous old workings while clearing out their new mine. S6, Ep6
Hit Or Miss. The Mooka Boys may lose a potential investor due to their little mining progress. Disaster strikes for the Opal Whisperers when Sofia's hoist fails. S6, Ep7
Thrill Of The Hunt. Pete and Kyle take the biggest gamble of their season, hunting valuable Tourmaline crystals. Hugh and Jarrin tackle the world's only Stitchtite quarry. S1, Ep6
Deadly Crocs - Dangerous Air. The Rockhounds hunt a rainforest river system by crocodile-infested waters. Plus, Jarrin and Hugh confront low oxygen levels and crumbling mine walls. S1, Ep7
Crystal Climax. In the final week of the season, Patrick gets an offer for their million-dollar Amethyst cluster while his team race to unearth $200,000 of crystals. S1, Ep8
The Gold Gypsies could be sitting on a fortune but must decide whether to take a huge gamble. A water shortage halts Shane and Russell's operations. S5, Ep10
The Goldtimers hire a 7-tonne loader to end their gold drought. The Dust Devils risk running out of water. Marcus vanishes while clifftop detecting. S5, Ep11
The Poseidon Crew hunts for bush gold. The Gold Gypsies face a tough decision. The Victoria Diggers' perseverance could finally pay off. S5, Ep12
Is That A Goat? Donny has been to jail twice because of his hoard. And while Joyce sees comfort in her doll collection, everyone else sees a creepy obsession. S3, Ep6
Tiny Monsters. Sherry's hoard has broken up her marriage. Now, authorities are threatening to take away her children and condemn her home. Can she break her bad habits? S3, Ep10
Mischievous Duende. Paranormal investigators capture a shadow figure in a haunted Nevada prison. A tiny elfin creature makes a toddler uneasy in Argentina. S6, Ep6
Lost Souls Of Kingman. The crew investigate an Arizona high school plagued by troubling paranormal experiences. Is this linked to an abandoned cemetery buried beneath the building? S20, Ep15
Old Bullion Plaza School. The crew unlock the dark secrets entombed in the walls of an old school. During the investigation, they capture some of their best evidence in years. S20, Ep16
The Alarming Asylum. In the UK, a trio of explorers visit an abandoned asylum. In New York, a family are freaked out by a door-slamming, doorbell-ringing phantom! S4, Ep8
Sirens In The Sea. A Massachusetts sailor is shocked to his core when a sinister sound calls out at sea. In the UK, a paranormal believer reveals her collection of ghost pictures. S4, Ep9

Diamonds in the Rough. The Baggage Battlers are back. Today they visit an auction in Brooklyn, one of the busiest shipping ports in the USA, but will they unearth any treasures? S2, Ep2
Breaking the Bank. The Baggage Battlers head to Atlanta, Georgia, to a freight auction where Mark spies some Rolls Royce aircraft parts, but will his bid secure the items? S2, Ep2
Greedy Pig. The buyers head south again, this time to the affluent Atlanta suburb of Alpharetta, seeking valuable items at a local Man Cave auction. But who will come away happy? S4, Ep6
Walk the Plank. Super Auctions collects some of the most iconic items from Orlando's star attractions and sells them to the highest bidder. How will the buyers get on? S4, Ep7
It's Not Easy Making Green. The buyers have travelled to Allentown in search of old money. Items up for grabs today include rare Civil War-era objects from Gettysburg. S4, Ep8
Dino Mite. Vintage advertising pits the buyers against each other in Knoxville, where Sally spends big to win a dinosaur. Meanwhile, Billy's attempt at sabotage backfires. S4, Ep9
Big Boy Bucks. The buyers take a gamble on vintage casino and advertising items, including a Bob's Big Boy statue in Vegas. Meanwhile, a rare Elvis recording could pay off big time. S4, Ep10
Gunning for Dollars. A giant Gatling gun and a rare advertising piece from Nabisco Cookies are among the items that interest the buyers at a gambling auction in Las Vegas. S4, Ep11
The Wizard of Odd. A lost property auction in reveals an old-school boom box from the 1980s, while a buyer is over the rainbow about a rare 'Wizard of Oz' piece in a sealed trunk. S4, Ep12
Safari Sale. The buyers visit South Africa for a once-in-a-lifetime auction, and Billy appraises a ceremonial mask. Will profit still be made outside the specialist's comfort zone? S4, Ep13
Porsche 4Cam Vs. Steve Jobs' BMW Z8. Wayne brings home a 1957 Porsche 356A 1500 GS Carrera with a rare four-camshaft engine. And, Apple guru Steve Jobs' 2000 BMW Z8 goes up for sale. S10, Ep1
Racing Record Monza, Bucking Bronco, And Vincent Motos. Wayne rescues a rare '59 Fiat Abarth Record Monza that been abandoned for 30 years. Plus, he finds a custom '66 Ford Bronco. S10, Ep2
One Car Wonder. It's Wayne's 1938 Lincoln Model K coupe vs. a 1938 Packard when Wayne and his friend compete at a car competition. Later, Wayne searches for the perfect Bugatti. S11, Ep1
3 Million Mile Volvo. Wayne lifts the lid on a Volvo that holds the world record for the highest mileage. Plus, he reverse engineers a gearless transmission for a 1912 Cartercar. S11, Ep5
Bobble-Head Ache. The 67 GTO is ready for its debut, but the team isn't sure about Dave's colour choice. Polished panels, custom upholstery and a fierce engine make it stand out. S4, Ep16
We Build Kindig Customs. Dave and the team start a one-of-a-kind build they have never attempted before, a 1964 Ranchero. But what there is underneath the metal sets the team back. S5, Ep1
24 Karat Magic. The Ranchero build is an epic achievement for Dave and the team, but will the client see it the same way? And will Dave find the perfect name for the perfect car? S5, Ep2
Armed with nothing but old hammers, Bangladeshi car designer Leepu and Cockney mechanic Bernie transform a heap into the ultimate super-car. S1, Ep1
Bernie and Leepu are looking for another rust bucket to turn into a super-car, but everything is in good condition. Luckily, a friend helps out. S1, Ep2

programmes.show_name: Extinct Or Alive: Land Of The Lost Sharks
programmes.show_description: Biologist Forrest Galante dives into treacherous, shark-infested waters in the southern hemisphere to rediscover three unique sharks lost to science for as long as 100 years.
Researchers try to make contact with bizarre alien sharks lurking in the deep. Pursuing the frilled shark, sleeper shark and cookie cutter shark brings unexpected encounters.
Mothman. A team of researchers seeks answers to mysteries surrounding the Mothman. They explore theories that the legendary cryptid is an abnormality in the evolutionary chain. S1, Ep3
Chupacabra. Experts analyse new evidence that could prove the legendary bloodsucking beast known as Chupacabra is real, and that there are two versions of the creature! S1, Ep8
